up|41|NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|There are special rules when bidding over 1NT overcall. Unlike over any other overcall, new suits by responder are not forcing. In fact they show a weakish hand, just willing to compete. If, for example the auction had gone 1@H-1@S-2@D by Ruth, that would have obviously been forcing. But the auction 1@H-1NT-2@D shows a weakish hand with long diamonds. |
PG| ***** 47 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|With a stronger hand Ruth would double. As to whether I would have bid 2@D vul with Ruth's hand, given her so-so 5-card suit, is not clear I probably pass and not bid 2@D. But 2@D is ok. |
PG| ***** 48 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|With usually 9 or more points, Ruth should double. The idea in bidding over 1NT is somewhat similar to what you do when it goes 1x-dbl-?. You redouble with a strong hand, and all other bids are weak. Similarly over 1NT, bids are weak, double is how you show a stronger hand.|
PG| ***** 49 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Next, let's discuss the play. Ruth can count on 3 diamond tricks if they are 4-2, 4 diamonds if they are 3-3, 2 clubs, and 1 spade. So she is probably going down 1 or 2. Personally, I would have pulled a 3rd trump with her hand, just in case they were 3-3.|
PG| ***** 50 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As to the defense, the spade lead was the best lead. However, in a suit contract, you lead high from a 2 card honor sequence, so Jacquie should have led the @SQ and Liza, when she gets in with a heart should definitely avoid playing hearts. I think her best play is the @SK and another spade. There is no point in setting up dummy's hearts. Partner is likely to have natural trump tricks since Ruth stopped drawing trumps.|
PG| ***** 51 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So all setting up hearts will do is allow Ruth to pitch losers while Jacquie ruffs with trump tricks she was entitled to any way. You normally don't want partner ruffing with natural trump tricks. Against best defense, 2@D should be down 2 - 200. I would guess E/W makes 1NT or 2NT. So -200 is 3 imps or so worse than letting them play 1N which is why I said I probably would not bid 2@D with Ruth's hand. Down 2 not vul is not so bad. But down 2 vul is usually a below average result in a part score hand.|
