^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|There is some controversy about Liza's bid. As I mentioned last hand, I play that any bid other than redouble (and 2NT which is a Jordan limit+ raise) shows less than 10 points. I think that is the easiest to remember and makes the most sense. Liza, your bid was fine. I am just discussing what it shows.|
PG| ***** 55 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Some experts, however, play a much more confusing style. They play 1-level bids over a double are forcing and unlimited. They may be weakish but they could be 10+ points and they play they are forcing. However (and this is what I think is confusing) they play 2-level bids are definitely weak and not forcing. So the auction 1@H-x-1@S potentially shows a stronger hand and is forcing. But the auction 1@H-x-2@C shows a weak hand and is not forcing. |
PG| ***** 56 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So I suggest you play what I do. With 10+ points you redouble or bid Jordan 2N as a limit+ raise. Any other bid is less than 10 and not forcing. BTW, I also play Bergen Raises over a takeout double (and therefore Jordan 2N shows a 3-card limit raise since 3@C shows a 4-card raise). However, that is optional. The important point is that bids other than redouble and Jordan 2N are less than 10.|
